WEBVTT

00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:17.960
Good day, brothers and sisters.

00:00:17.960 --> 00:00:19.960
We will begin this convention session

00:00:19.960 --> 00:00:23.960
by enjoying another music video presentation.

00:00:23.960 --> 00:00:28.960
This video highlights the power that faith can have in our lives.

00:00:28.960 --> 00:00:30.960
Please enjoy the video.

00:00:30.960 --> 00:10:36.250
Our opening song expresses our joy and practicing true worship.

00:10:36.250 --> 00:10:42.250
Let's sing song number 24 entitled Come to Jehovah's Mountain.

00:10:42.250 --> 00:13:27.460
That song number 24.

00:13:27.460 --> 00:13:30.460
Genuine faith moves us to action.

00:13:30.460 --> 00:13:34.460
This could be seen in the lives of our brothers and sisters Earthwide.

00:13:34.460 --> 00:13:41.460
Please enjoy the following video that features experiences from six different regions.

00:13:41.460 --> 00:13:44.460
Let's see how our brothers are showing faith.

00:13:44.460 --> 00:13:56.539
They defeated kingdoms.

00:13:56.539 --> 00:13:59.539
Brought about righteousness.

00:13:59.539 --> 00:14:01.539
Obtained promises.

00:14:01.539 --> 00:14:04.539
Stopped the mouths of lions.

00:14:04.539 --> 00:14:07.539
Quenched the force of fire.

00:14:07.539 --> 00:14:10.539
Escaped the edge of the sword.

00:14:10.539 --> 00:14:13.539
From a weak state were made powerful.

00:14:13.539 --> 00:14:19.539
Became mighty in war, routed invading armies.

00:14:19.539 --> 00:14:26.539
Faith in Jehovah has allowed ordinary people to do extraordinary things.

00:14:26.539 --> 00:14:30.539
This kind of faith is still active today

00:14:30.539 --> 00:14:35.539
and still has the power to help us through any difficulty.

00:14:35.539 --> 00:14:38.539
So let's travel across the globe

00:14:38.539 --> 00:14:46.539
and see how deep reliance on Jehovah has helped many overcome their unique trials.

00:14:46.539 --> 00:14:52.539
As we visit each land, we'll enjoy a story of faith

00:14:52.539 --> 00:14:59.539
shared both from the perspective of close friends as well as the individuals involved.

00:14:59.539 --> 00:15:09.750
Now to our first destination.

00:15:09.750 --> 00:15:15.750
South Africa is full of contrasts and diversity.

00:15:15.750 --> 00:15:19.750
Big modern cities mix with poorer remote areas.

00:15:19.750 --> 00:15:22.750
For many volunteers in Kingdom Hall construction,

00:15:22.750 --> 00:15:25.750
this presents wonderful opportunities

00:15:25.750 --> 00:15:29.750
but also unique challenges that require faith in Jehovah.

00:15:29.750 --> 00:15:33.750
An example of that is our young friend, Nathla.

00:15:33.750 --> 00:15:39.750
My wife and I really appreciated the faith she showed to make herself available

00:15:39.750 --> 00:15:42.750
and to keep her joy in her assignment.

00:15:42.750 --> 00:15:47.750
I'm the only Jehovah's Witness in my family.

00:15:47.750 --> 00:15:52.750
What my mother desired the most for me was to grow up,

00:15:52.750 --> 00:15:58.750
go to college, and in time, get a high-paying job.

00:15:58.750 --> 00:16:04.029
My congregation was busy building a Kingdom Hall.

00:16:04.029 --> 00:16:07.029
So I would sometimes also go to help.

00:16:07.029 --> 00:16:14.500
I wanted to see and feel the joy that those brothers were having building Kingdom Halls.

00:16:14.500 --> 00:16:20.500
My mom didn't like it when she heard that I was going to help with Kingdom Hall construction.

00:16:20.500 --> 00:16:24.500
She felt that I was wasting my time.

00:16:24.500 --> 00:16:30.980
When I arrived on site, everything I did was for the first time.

00:16:30.980 --> 00:16:35.980
I didn't have skills and I had never done this work before.

00:16:35.980 --> 00:16:37.980
It is not easy.

00:16:37.980 --> 00:16:43.980
Sometimes I get tired, mentally exhausted, and even physically exhausted.

00:16:43.980 --> 00:16:46.980
Sometimes it's difficult to even read the Bible.

00:16:46.980 --> 00:16:52.980
I just want to wash up and go to sleep.

00:16:52.980 --> 00:16:57.980
It was important for Nathla to find her spiritual balance

00:16:57.980 --> 00:17:04.980
because her spirituality was more important than working hard on site.

00:17:04.980 --> 00:17:08.980
I realized that I needed to be really determined

00:17:08.980 --> 00:17:12.980
because my spirituality was not the same as before.

00:17:12.980 --> 00:17:16.980
I saw that I needed to make a change.

00:17:16.980 --> 00:17:20.980
I made it a priority to read the Bible first

00:17:20.980 --> 00:17:23.980
and to think about the things I read.

00:17:23.980 --> 00:17:30.829
I also made sure that I was regular in going out in the ministry.

00:17:30.829 --> 00:17:37.829
Prayer helped a lot because prayer is the best way for me to tell Jehovah things that concern me.

00:17:37.829 --> 00:17:42.829
I have seen from myself how Jehovah God has sustained me.

00:17:42.829 --> 00:17:47.829
We've seen that she is much more balanced.

00:17:47.829 --> 00:17:52.829
My mom would phone and ask, Nathla, how is the project going?

00:17:52.829 --> 00:17:58.829
And then she would say, if this makes you happy, then I am also happy.

00:17:58.829 --> 00:18:02.829
At first, I had my fears, but faith made me confident

00:18:02.829 --> 00:18:08.829
that Jehovah God would always be there to support me in everything I do.

00:18:08.829 --> 00:18:32.220
Canada is a diverse country, both the landscape

00:18:32.220 --> 00:18:36.220
and because of immigration, the people in their languages.

00:18:36.220 --> 00:18:39.220
In order to share Bible truth with these ones,

00:18:39.220 --> 00:18:44.220
many brothers are learning a new language like my friend Shaquille.

00:18:44.220 --> 00:18:52.619
When Shaquille got invited to Bethel, I had the privilege of serving at Canada branch at the time.

00:18:52.619 --> 00:18:56.619
So it was such a pleasure to see this young man who had all these wonderful goals

00:18:56.619 --> 00:19:00.619
and to see one by one Jehovah opening those doors to him.

00:19:00.619 --> 00:19:04.619
He had made a promise to Jehovah as a young person.

00:19:04.619 --> 00:19:10.619
I want to help those that don't have anyone to help them.

00:19:10.619 --> 00:19:14.619
Jehovah saw good in me and he invested in me and he was very patient with me

00:19:14.619 --> 00:19:18.619
and I saw it through every brother and sister who sincerely reached out to help me.

00:19:18.619 --> 00:19:22.619
I'm meditating on Jehovah's qualities and you want to imitate him.

00:19:22.619 --> 00:19:25.619
You want to show the kindness that he's shown towards you towards others.

00:19:25.619 --> 00:19:29.619
So in foreign language, I feel like there's a giant opportunity to do that.

00:19:29.619 --> 00:19:32.619
I started to learn Punjabi and I never regretted it.

00:19:32.619 --> 00:19:35.619
It changed my service to Jehovah.

00:19:35.619 --> 00:19:45.430
There was a time period in my Bethel service when I was really, really sick

00:19:45.430 --> 00:19:49.430
and it was a kind of sickness where I didn't know why it was happening.

00:19:49.430 --> 00:19:52.430
No doctor could tell me why it was happening.

00:19:52.430 --> 00:19:58.430
It affected my physical appearance and it seemed like torment throughout each and every day.

00:19:58.430 --> 00:20:03.430
A lot of times I would have rather not been seen.

00:20:03.430 --> 00:20:07.430
So serving in foreign language now when you're one of the people who spiritually

00:20:07.430 --> 00:20:11.430
supposed to be strengthening others, you're going through a hard time yourself.

00:20:11.430 --> 00:20:14.430
That was a massive challenge for me.

00:20:14.430 --> 00:20:21.430
I think all of his friends just really appreciated the faith that he had to overcome that

00:20:21.430 --> 00:20:27.430
and even though it was a very low point in his life, he really hung on to Jehovah.

00:20:27.430 --> 00:20:31.430
If I'm in this assignment and I've seen that Jehovah's bless me,

00:20:31.430 --> 00:20:35.430
what would lead me to conclude that he's going to stop?

00:20:35.430 --> 00:20:40.430
He couldn't sleep. He just couldn't continue at Bethel either.

00:20:40.430 --> 00:20:44.430
I had left Bethel but still my health was decreasing and it was getting really bad.

00:20:44.430 --> 00:20:48.430
And it was getting to the point that doctors expressed concern about maybe

00:20:48.430 --> 00:20:51.430
an organ failing and things like that.

00:20:51.430 --> 00:20:55.430
But they did not give me any way out. I had no way out.

00:20:55.430 --> 00:21:01.430
He kept making progress even though there was certainly some really difficult times for him.

00:21:01.430 --> 00:21:05.430
I had to take a realistic approach towards my new situation

00:21:05.430 --> 00:21:10.430
and I had to figure out how am I going to put Kingdom interest first

00:21:10.430 --> 00:21:17.430
while materially taking care of myself and hopefully figuring out why I'm sick

00:21:17.430 --> 00:21:20.430
and if I can do anything about it.

00:21:20.430 --> 00:21:25.430
In the end he decided to stick with foreign language

00:21:25.430 --> 00:21:31.430
and something I really learned from Shaquille is that he really took the scriptures

00:21:31.430 --> 00:21:37.430
and made it personal. He would read it as if he was the person in the scriptures

00:21:37.430 --> 00:21:43.430
and he would meditate on it and now he could see how even though he didn't know the answers

00:21:43.430 --> 00:21:47.430
Jehovah would help him through his difficult times.

00:21:47.430 --> 00:21:52.430
So what am I going to do? I'm going to live up to what I promised to Jehovah.

00:21:52.430 --> 00:21:56.430
Today he serves with his wife in the Punjabi field.

00:21:56.430 --> 00:22:01.430
He's a loving shepherd and he even instructs Punjabi language classes.

00:22:01.430 --> 00:22:26.009
In Indonesia people work very hard.

00:22:26.009 --> 00:22:29.009
They seek stability through a secure job.

00:22:29.009 --> 00:22:33.009
This can have a powerful influence on the brothers and sisters

00:22:33.009 --> 00:22:37.009
because they may feel that they can't expand their ministry.

00:22:37.009 --> 00:22:42.009
When I met the Japanese girls they were working toward Pioneer service.

00:22:42.009 --> 00:22:45.009
When they started I asked them,

00:22:45.009 --> 00:22:49.009
would you like to be used more fully by Jehovah?

00:22:49.009 --> 00:22:52.009
I was confused.

00:22:52.009 --> 00:22:58.009
We felt that the Pioneer service itself was already a big accomplishment.

00:22:58.009 --> 00:23:03.009
I encouraged them to think about the school for Kingdom Evangelizers.

00:23:03.009 --> 00:23:08.009
I had never imagined applying for SKE.

00:23:08.009 --> 00:23:10.009
It was tempting.

00:23:10.009 --> 00:23:13.009
I wanted to be used by Jehovah,

00:23:13.009 --> 00:23:18.009
but what would happen to us after graduation?

00:23:18.009 --> 00:23:22.289
Where would we be assigned?

00:23:22.289 --> 00:23:26.599
What would be our assignment?

00:23:26.599 --> 00:23:30.680
We needed more faith,

00:23:30.680 --> 00:23:33.680
so we prayed a lot about that.

00:23:33.680 --> 00:23:38.680
Jehovah answered my prayers through the brothers and sisters in the congregation.

00:23:38.680 --> 00:23:43.119
Marta had a prestigious job.

00:23:43.119 --> 00:23:48.119
She was even being offered many scholarships so that she could pursue higher education

00:23:48.119 --> 00:23:51.119
and further advance her career.

00:23:51.119 --> 00:23:56.119
The brothers and sisters never criticized Marta's work choice.

00:23:56.119 --> 00:24:02.119
Rather they showed us the joys of serving Jehovah more fully.

00:24:02.119 --> 00:24:05.119
When I was still deciding what to do,

00:24:05.119 --> 00:24:08.119
some of them asked me about my spiritual goals,

00:24:08.119 --> 00:24:11.119
and what I could see myself doing,

00:24:11.119 --> 00:24:14.119
thinking about such questions,

00:24:14.119 --> 00:24:19.589
convinced me to choose SKE.

00:24:19.589 --> 00:24:22.589
They were invited to attend the school.

00:24:22.589 --> 00:24:25.589
They had to leave their jobs, their house,

00:24:25.589 --> 00:24:28.589
and the comforts of the place and city where they lived.

00:24:28.589 --> 00:24:31.589
They were assigned to a small congregation.

00:24:31.589 --> 00:24:38.589
They had to pray even more to ask Jehovah God for guidance and direction.

00:24:38.589 --> 00:24:44.589
Now they're serving in the traveling work, caring for a certain.

00:24:44.589 --> 00:24:49.589
We are fully convinced that it was not due to any greatness on our part,

00:24:49.589 --> 00:24:53.589
but because of Jehovah's help.

00:24:53.589 --> 00:24:56.589
If we want to be used by Jehovah,

00:24:56.589 --> 00:24:59.589
and if we want to serve him,

00:24:59.589 --> 00:25:03.589
Jehovah can use us in many different ways.

00:25:03.589 --> 00:25:26.569
BG is a beautiful place.

00:25:26.569 --> 00:25:34.200
However, one thing that is common here is poverty.

00:25:34.200 --> 00:25:40.200
That is the situation sister Baccata faces.

00:25:40.200 --> 00:25:45.930
My husband was a hard worker.

00:25:45.930 --> 00:25:47.930
While we were out in the water,

00:25:47.930 --> 00:25:50.930
he cried out from the mangroves.

00:25:50.930 --> 00:25:53.930
When I went and found him,

00:25:53.930 --> 00:25:58.930
I knew that it was a stroke.

00:25:58.930 --> 00:26:03.930
I had to take on both roles as husband and wife.

00:26:03.930 --> 00:26:05.930
I would farm.

00:26:05.930 --> 00:26:07.930
I would fish.

00:26:07.930 --> 00:26:10.930
It was a difficult life.

00:26:10.930 --> 00:26:18.640
One day, a sister was sick.

00:26:18.640 --> 00:26:22.640
Even though sister Baccata faced challenges,

00:26:22.640 --> 00:26:27.640
if there was any washing or cleaning needed for the sick sister,

00:26:27.640 --> 00:26:34.809
she was happy to go and help with that too.

00:26:34.809 --> 00:26:42.779
I think back to when a cyclone hit Kadavu, cyclone Kenny.

00:26:42.779 --> 00:26:46.779
I was scared by the damage it did to our house.

00:26:46.779 --> 00:26:50.779
Our outdoor kitchen was blown off.

00:26:50.779 --> 00:26:54.779
When I heard about the things that happened to the brothers,

00:26:54.779 --> 00:26:57.779
I felt so sorry for them.

00:26:57.779 --> 00:27:02.059
Their roofs were blown away,

00:27:02.059 --> 00:27:04.059
and the walls had fallen down.

00:27:04.059 --> 00:27:12.039
Just think about what sister Baccata did.

00:27:12.039 --> 00:27:16.349
She had 20 Fiji and dollars.

00:27:16.349 --> 00:27:19.349
That is the only money she had.

00:27:19.349 --> 00:27:25.779
But she decided to give all of that to the brothers.

00:27:25.779 --> 00:27:33.630
I didn't have any other way to help them.

00:27:33.630 --> 00:27:36.630
Jehovah is the God of love.

00:27:36.630 --> 00:27:39.630
Like it says at first on four and eight,

00:27:39.630 --> 00:27:42.630
his main quality is love.

00:27:42.630 --> 00:27:44.630
Because of that love,

00:27:44.630 --> 00:27:49.740
I gave the money from the bottom of my heart.

00:27:49.740 --> 00:27:53.740
I learned that even though we are poor,

00:27:53.740 --> 00:27:59.920
we can still be generous to sister brothers.

00:27:59.920 --> 00:28:01.920
The more I gave,

00:28:01.920 --> 00:28:05.920
the more Jehovah gave back to me.

00:28:05.920 --> 00:28:07.920
Till today,

00:28:07.920 --> 00:28:10.920
we've always had what we've needed.

00:28:10.920 --> 00:28:34.039
And through,

00:28:34.039 --> 00:28:36.039
like many places around the world,

00:28:36.039 --> 00:28:39.039
our brothers and sisters need to work hard.

00:28:39.039 --> 00:28:48.259
Benjamin and Doris have to make good use of their resources

00:28:48.259 --> 00:28:51.259
in order to provide for their family.

00:28:51.259 --> 00:28:57.079
We want to give our children a spiritual heritage.

00:28:57.079 --> 00:28:59.079
We want them to be able to serve Jehovah

00:28:59.079 --> 00:29:01.079
by watching how we are doing it.

00:29:01.079 --> 00:29:05.579
We watch a lot of videos that help us.

00:29:05.579 --> 00:29:09.579
We often remember the video about Abilio Anula.

00:29:09.579 --> 00:29:11.579
They also had three children.

00:29:11.579 --> 00:29:13.579
They moved to another place

00:29:13.579 --> 00:29:17.579
and grew up in a very nice spiritual atmosphere.

00:29:17.579 --> 00:29:19.579
They are serving Jehovah now as adults.

00:29:19.579 --> 00:29:23.250
So we asked ourselves,

00:29:23.250 --> 00:29:26.250
could we move to another place where the need is great?

00:29:26.250 --> 00:29:31.619
It takes faith to go to an unfamiliar place.

00:29:31.619 --> 00:29:35.619
When video on JW.org that helped us a lot

00:29:35.619 --> 00:29:38.619
was about the family from England that moved to Ecuador.

00:29:38.619 --> 00:29:40.619
First, they went for one month.

00:29:40.619 --> 00:29:43.619
So we said that we should also go as a first.

00:29:43.619 --> 00:29:46.619
Going to another country would have been exciting.

00:29:46.619 --> 00:29:48.619
It would have been super.

00:29:48.619 --> 00:29:54.619
But our economic situation wouldn't allow us to go that far.

00:29:54.619 --> 00:29:56.619
We took a trip together with our children

00:29:56.619 --> 00:30:00.619
to visit a territory that had a need, called Kalango.

00:30:00.619 --> 00:30:04.619
It takes about an hour and a half to get there.

00:30:04.619 --> 00:30:08.619
They liked the geography of the area in all the vegetation.

00:30:08.619 --> 00:30:11.619
There were many things that captured their attention.

00:30:11.619 --> 00:30:16.619
The things that I like in Kalango are playing and preaching.

00:30:16.619 --> 00:30:23.470
We were unable to move to the city of Kalango

00:30:23.470 --> 00:30:27.470
because of the economic situation that the people face there.

00:30:27.470 --> 00:30:29.470
It's hard to get a job there.

00:30:29.470 --> 00:30:31.470
So for that reason,

00:30:31.470 --> 00:30:36.470
we decided to travel to Kalango Friday, Saturday and Sunday.

00:30:36.470 --> 00:30:39.470
And work the other days here in Pachakamak.

00:30:39.470 --> 00:30:43.470
We have felt that Jehovah is helping us

00:30:43.470 --> 00:30:46.470
because he has made it possible to work here

00:30:46.470 --> 00:30:49.470
and the money that we earn in those days

00:30:49.470 --> 00:30:53.470
allows us to be with our brothers there.

00:30:53.470 --> 00:30:56.470
We needed to know how to keep things simple.

00:30:56.470 --> 00:31:00.470
We learned that from the videos on JW.org.

00:31:00.470 --> 00:31:03.470
The hard work that they do proves to me

00:31:03.470 --> 00:31:05.470
that they really love Jehovah.

00:31:05.470 --> 00:31:09.470
They fully trust that Jehovah is our father.

00:31:09.470 --> 00:31:10.470
He is the dad.

00:31:10.470 --> 00:31:14.470
And we know that dad always comes through for his children.

00:31:14.470 --> 00:31:18.470
And that faith is something that greatly motivates them.

00:31:18.470 --> 00:31:22.470
The videos on JW.org have given us the push that we needed.

00:31:22.470 --> 00:31:26.720
We needed those videos in order to take action

00:31:26.720 --> 00:31:29.720
and move to another area.

00:31:29.720 --> 00:31:49.160
Across Russia,

00:31:49.160 --> 00:31:55.160
our brothers have successfully faced decades of persecution and ban.

00:31:55.160 --> 00:31:59.160
The budden chucks, like so many families there,

00:31:59.160 --> 00:32:03.160
still face these challenges today.

00:32:03.160 --> 00:32:08.160
On June 12, 2018, at 5.30 a.m.,

00:32:08.160 --> 00:32:12.160
armed men burst into our home.

00:32:12.160 --> 00:32:18.660
They threw my husband to the floor and handcuffed him.

00:32:19.660 --> 00:32:21.660
Eventually, they sent my husband

00:32:21.660 --> 00:32:25.660
to a pretrial detention facility for 11 months.

00:32:25.660 --> 00:32:29.660
It was frightening just imagining certain things.

00:32:29.660 --> 00:32:33.660
She didn't find it easy and shed many tears.

00:32:33.660 --> 00:32:37.660
I was really worried about how I would care for the children

00:32:37.660 --> 00:32:42.660
and how I would fulfill their needs spiritually, emotionally, and physically.

00:32:42.660 --> 00:32:46.099
Prayer calmed me down.

00:32:47.099 --> 00:32:52.099
Because I wanted, of course, to react very emotionally to everything

00:32:52.099 --> 00:32:55.099
to the injustice that we were facing.

00:32:55.099 --> 00:32:58.099
When the court hearings were going on,

00:32:58.099 --> 00:33:00.099
brothers and sisters would come.

00:33:00.099 --> 00:33:08.009
It was such a support, so strengthening.

00:33:08.009 --> 00:33:11.009
On September 19, 2019,

00:33:11.009 --> 00:33:15.009
the court convicted my husband

00:33:15.009 --> 00:33:19.009
and sent him to a prison colony for three and a half years.

00:33:19.009 --> 00:33:28.180
In January 2020, a new disaster hit us.

00:33:28.180 --> 00:33:33.180
At 1 a.m., our house burned to the ground.

00:33:33.180 --> 00:33:37.180
We stood there near the house,

00:33:37.180 --> 00:33:42.180
and my son Igor suggested saying a prayer.

00:33:42.180 --> 00:33:47.180
I don't remember the prayer, but afterwards I felt calmer.

00:33:47.180 --> 00:33:50.180
Then cars started coming to the house.

00:33:50.180 --> 00:33:55.180
Our brothers and sisters, I was frozen, shaking from the cold.

00:33:55.180 --> 00:33:59.180
