and thus we may feel inadequate

01:12:48.420 --> 01:12:53.420
to assist with a local design construction or other project.

01:12:53.420 --> 01:12:57.420
Or two, we may also realize that to begin assisting,

01:12:57.420 --> 01:13:01.420
generally, we do so on a temporary basis.

01:13:01.420 --> 01:13:04.420
Therefore, we may have concerns about leaving our job

01:13:04.420 --> 01:13:08.420
or our family for a period of time to assist.

01:13:08.420 --> 01:13:11.420
Well, if you can relate to those concerns

01:13:11.420 --> 01:13:13.420
and note out the example of Nehemiah

01:13:13.420 --> 01:13:15.420
will build your faith.

01:13:15.420 --> 01:13:20.420
Turn please to Nehemiah chapter 1, verse 2 and 3.

01:13:20.420 --> 01:13:23.420
Nehemiah 1, 2 and 3.

01:13:23.420 --> 01:13:27.420
At that time, Haneinai, one of my brothers,

01:13:27.420 --> 01:13:30.420
arrived with other men from Judah,

01:13:30.420 --> 01:13:32.420
and I asked him about the remaining Jews

01:13:32.420 --> 01:13:36.420
who had escaped the captivity and also about Jerusalem.

01:13:36.420 --> 01:13:40.420
They replied, those remaining there in the province

01:13:40.420 --> 01:13:44.420
who have survived the captivity are in a terrible situation

01:13:44.420 --> 01:13:48.420
and in disgrace, the walls of Jerusalem are broken down

01:13:48.420 --> 01:13:51.420
and its gates have been burned with fire.

01:13:51.420 --> 01:13:54.420
Nehemiah here is presented with a knee.

01:13:54.420 --> 01:13:55.420
What would he do?

01:13:55.420 --> 01:13:58.420
Would he say, oh, I hope those skilled brothers

01:13:58.420 --> 01:14:00.420
were in that situation one day.

01:14:00.420 --> 01:14:03.420
Look at chapter 2 and verse 5.

01:14:03.420 --> 01:14:05.420
I then said to the king,

01:14:05.420 --> 01:14:07.420
if it pleases the king

01:14:07.420 --> 01:14:10.420
and if your servant has found favor with you,

01:14:10.420 --> 01:14:13.420
send me to Judah to the city

01:14:13.420 --> 01:14:15.420
where my forefathers are buried

01:14:15.420 --> 01:14:18.420
so that I may rebuild it.

01:14:18.420 --> 01:14:19.420
Yes, Nehemiah was moved.

01:14:19.420 --> 01:14:21.420
He wanted to help.

01:14:21.420 --> 01:14:23.420
He saw an opportunity

01:14:23.420 --> 01:14:25.420
and demonstrated his faith.

01:14:25.420 --> 01:14:27.420
He took the initiative.

01:14:28.420 --> 01:14:32.420
Now, did it take faith for Nehemiah to take this step?

01:14:32.420 --> 01:14:33.420
Well, no doubt it did.

01:14:33.420 --> 01:14:35.420
Why do we say that?

01:14:35.420 --> 01:14:38.420
Well, first off, what was Nehemiah's work assignment?

01:14:38.420 --> 01:14:42.420
Was he the head of the King's construction project?

01:14:42.420 --> 01:14:46.420
Was he the leading architect or engineer or city planner?

01:14:46.420 --> 01:14:47.420
No.

01:14:47.420 --> 01:14:51.420
No, rather, he was the cup bearer to the king.

01:14:51.420 --> 01:14:52.420
You can picture him saying,

01:14:52.420 --> 01:14:54.420
well, I don't have the experience

01:14:54.420 --> 01:14:56.420
to rebuild the walls of Jerusalem.

01:14:56.420 --> 01:14:57.420
I don't know where to start.

01:14:57.420 --> 01:15:00.420
Maybe I best leave that to somebody else.

01:15:00.420 --> 01:15:02.420
No, rather, he saw the need.

01:15:02.420 --> 01:15:04.420
He had the circumstances to help

01:15:04.420 --> 01:15:07.420
and he acted on that need.

01:15:07.420 --> 01:15:09.420
At Nehemiah did not let his possible

01:15:09.420 --> 01:15:12.420
lack of experience hold him back.

01:15:12.420 --> 01:15:14.420
That took faith.

01:15:14.420 --> 01:15:18.420
Now, what about the fact that this was only a temporary assignment?

01:15:18.420 --> 01:15:20.420
Well, Nehemiah again was willing

01:15:20.420 --> 01:15:22.420
to leave his prestigious position

01:15:22.420 --> 01:15:24.420
as the cup bearer to the king.

01:15:24.420 --> 01:15:25.420
You think about it?

01:15:25.420 --> 01:15:27.420
He could have wondered whether his replacement

01:15:27.420 --> 01:15:30.420
would take over his position permanently.

01:15:30.420 --> 01:15:32.420
Would his nice job be there

01:15:32.420 --> 01:15:35.420
when he returned from Jerusalem?

01:15:35.420 --> 01:15:37.420
Well, Nehemiah showed faith

01:15:37.420 --> 01:15:40.420
that Jehovah had loyal love

01:15:40.420 --> 01:15:42.420
and would remember him.

01:15:42.420 --> 01:15:46.420
Notice his words in Nehemiah chapter 1 and verse 5.

01:15:46.420 --> 01:15:48.420
I said,

01:15:48.420 --> 01:15:50.420
Oh, Jehovah, the God of the heavens,

01:15:50.420 --> 01:15:53.420
the great and awe-inspiring God,

01:15:53.420 --> 01:15:55.420
who keeps his covenant

01:15:55.420 --> 01:15:58.420
and shows loyal love to those who love him

01:15:58.420 --> 01:16:01.420
and keep his commandments.

01:16:01.420 --> 01:16:02.420
Yes, Nehemiah was confident

01:16:02.420 --> 01:16:05.420
Jehovah would show loyal love.

01:16:05.420 --> 01:16:07.420
Jehovah would work things out.

01:16:07.420 --> 01:16:10.420
And what was the result of Nehemiah's faith?

01:16:10.420 --> 01:16:14.420
Well, although at first Nehemiah was not known as a builder,

01:16:14.420 --> 01:16:16.420
Jehovah used him in a mighty way

01:16:16.420 --> 01:16:18.420
to accomplish, as well.

01:16:18.420 --> 01:16:20.420
And Nehemiah contributed to the rebuilding

01:16:20.420 --> 01:16:22.420
of the walls of Jerusalem

01:16:22.420 --> 01:16:25.420
in significant ways.

01:16:25.420 --> 01:16:27.420
What's the lesson?

01:16:27.420 --> 01:16:30.420
Well, the lesson is we need faith

01:16:30.420 --> 01:16:31.420
if we are going to assist

01:16:31.420 --> 01:16:34.420
with a Theocratic building project.

01:16:34.420 --> 01:16:36.420
Now, primarily, we need brothers and sisters

01:16:36.420 --> 01:16:39.420
who have a strong relationship with Jehovah

01:16:39.420 --> 01:16:40.420
and a willing spirit.

01:16:40.420 --> 01:16:42.420
Those are the qualities we need.

01:16:42.420 --> 01:16:46.420
A construction or technical skills can be learned.

01:16:46.420 --> 01:16:49.420
And strong faith will give us the confidence

01:16:49.420 --> 01:16:51.420
that if we are invited,

01:16:51.420 --> 01:16:54.420
Jehovah will make us equal to the task

01:16:54.420 --> 01:16:57.420
and help us to develop the skills that are needed.

01:16:57.420 --> 01:17:00.420
