01:23:05.010 --> 01:23:07.010
There is no other organization

01:23:07.010 --> 01:23:10.010
that compares to Jehovah's organization.

01:23:10.010 --> 01:23:12.010
Everything the organization provides

01:23:12.010 --> 01:23:15.010
and helps with is free of charge.

01:23:15.010 --> 01:23:18.010
But Jehovah invites all of us to give to him

01:23:18.010 --> 01:23:20.010
or contribute our material resources

01:23:20.010 --> 01:23:23.010
according to what we personally decide.

01:23:23.010 --> 01:23:27.010
Now, why is this giving a matter of faith?

01:23:27.010 --> 01:23:29.010
Could it be that we hold back

01:23:29.010 --> 01:23:32.010
because one,

01:23:32.010 --> 01:23:34.010
we might feel that if we are generous,

01:23:34.010 --> 01:23:37.010
we might not have enough for our own needs.

01:23:37.010 --> 01:23:39.010
To think this way is understandable.

01:23:39.010 --> 01:23:41.010
Life is unpredictable,

01:23:41.010 --> 01:23:43.010
and nobody knows what the future holds

01:23:43.010 --> 01:23:47.010
and what our material needs might be tomorrow.

01:23:47.010 --> 01:23:50.010
Or could it be that we hold back too?

01:23:50.010 --> 01:23:52.010
Because we feel that our personal contribution

01:23:52.010 --> 01:23:56.010
is so small and therefore insignificant.

01:23:56.010 --> 01:23:59.010
Maybe we have very little material

01:23:59.010 --> 01:24:01.010
because we live in a poor country.

01:24:01.010 --> 01:24:05.010
Or we struggle to cover our expenses for other reasons.

01:24:05.010 --> 01:24:09.010
So we see that our giving really depends

01:24:09.010 --> 01:24:12.010
on how we connect this with Jehovah.

01:24:12.010 --> 01:24:14.010
Our view of Jehovah,

01:24:14.010 --> 01:24:16.010
our friendship with Jehovah

01:24:16.010 --> 01:24:19.010
needs to influence our actions

01:24:19.010 --> 01:24:22.010
and this requires faith.

01:24:22.010 --> 01:24:26.010
Therefore, let us briefly look at these two concerns

01:24:26.010 --> 01:24:28.010
that might impact our generosity

01:24:28.010 --> 01:24:31.010
and how faith can help us.

01:24:31.010 --> 01:24:34.010
Now, the first concern was the uncertainty

01:24:34.010 --> 01:24:36.010
of our own future needs.

01:24:36.010 --> 01:24:41.010
Please let us open our Bible to 1 Corinthians 16.

01:24:41.010 --> 01:24:43.010
Here in our theme scripture,

01:24:43.010 --> 01:24:44.010
the Apostle Paul,

01:24:44.010 --> 01:24:46.010
provides a principle to follow

01:24:46.010 --> 01:24:48.010
when we consider donations.

01:24:48.010 --> 01:24:50.010
This is 1 Corinthians 16,

01:24:50.010 --> 01:24:53.010
and we read verse 2.

01:24:53.010 --> 01:24:56.010
On the first day of every week,

01:24:56.010 --> 01:24:59.010
each of you should set something aside

01:24:59.010 --> 01:25:01.010
according to his own means

01:25:01.010 --> 01:25:03.010
so that collections will not take place

01:25:03.010 --> 01:25:05.010
when I arrive.

01:25:05.010 --> 01:25:08.010
So the Apostle Paul encouraged Christians

01:25:08.010 --> 01:25:10.010
to plan ahead to give.

01:25:10.010 --> 01:25:12.010
In other words, Paul wanted them

01:25:12.010 --> 01:25:14.010
to consider their circumstances

01:25:14.010 --> 01:25:17.010
and to decide on a certain contribution amount.

01:25:17.010 --> 01:25:19.010
Paul was convinced

01:25:19.010 --> 01:25:21.010
that this would not result

01:25:21.010 --> 01:25:23.010
in their lacking material necessities.

01:25:23.010 --> 01:25:25.010
He himself had experienced

01:25:25.010 --> 01:25:26.010
not from Jehovah,

01:25:26.010 --> 01:25:30.010
and he knew that God would care for them.

01:25:30.010 --> 01:25:33.010
Generous giving would further allow Jehovah

01:25:33.010 --> 01:25:37.420
to care for them in a generous way.

01:25:37.420 --> 01:25:39.420
Do we now see how planning ahead

01:25:39.420 --> 01:25:42.420
is an expression of our faith?

01:25:42.420 --> 01:25:43.420
When we do this,

01:25:43.420 --> 01:25:46.420
we are putting Jehovah to the test in a good way.

01:25:46.420 --> 01:25:48.420
We want to experience how it feels

01:25:48.420 --> 01:25:51.420
when Jehovah sees us setting the right priorities

01:25:51.420 --> 01:25:54.420
and in turn becomes our protector

01:25:54.420 --> 01:25:57.420
and our rewarder.

01:25:57.420 --> 01:25:59.420
Dear brothers and sisters,

01:25:59.420 --> 01:26:02.420
you are displaying this kind of faith.

01:26:02.420 --> 01:26:04.420
Many of you set something aside

01:26:04.420 --> 01:26:05.420
so that you can contribute

01:26:05.420 --> 01:26:08.420
when you come to the Kingdom Hall.

01:26:08.420 --> 01:26:10.420
Others consider their expenses

01:26:10.420 --> 01:26:11.420
and their financial means

01:26:11.420 --> 01:26:15.420
and they decide to regularly donate electronically.

01:26:15.420 --> 01:26:18.420
Even when circumstances have not allowed you

01:26:18.420 --> 01:26:20.420
to donate the way you've done in the past,

01:26:20.420 --> 01:26:24.420
you still find a way to give your contribution to Jehovah.

01:26:24.420 --> 01:26:29.420
Jehovah promised to care for our needs.

01:26:29.420 --> 01:26:32.420
Do we really believe that?

01:26:32.420 --> 01:26:34.420
If we do,

01:26:34.420 --> 01:26:39.420
our faith will help us to give generously.

01:26:39.420 --> 01:26:41.420
There was a second concern

01:26:41.420 --> 01:26:43.420
that might hold us back from giving generously.

01:26:43.420 --> 01:26:45.420
We might consider our circumstances

01:26:45.420 --> 01:26:48.420
and feel that the contribution we can make

01:26:48.420 --> 01:26:53.420
is so small that it makes no difference.

01:26:53.420 --> 01:26:57.420
Do you still have 1 Corinthians 16 verse 2 open?

01:26:57.420 --> 01:26:58.420
What did we read there?

01:26:58.420 --> 01:27:00.420
Let us read it again.

01:27:00.420 --> 01:27:04.420
1 Corinthians 16 verse 2.

01:27:04.420 --> 01:27:06.420
On the first day of every week,

01:27:06.420 --> 01:27:10.420
each of you should set something aside

01:27:10.420 --> 01:27:14.420
according to his own means.

01:27:14.420 --> 01:27:16.420
Did you notice Paul did not specify

01:27:16.420 --> 01:27:19.420
a certain minimum amount?

01:27:19.420 --> 01:27:20.420
And later,

01:27:20.420 --> 01:27:22.420
he mentioned that Macedonian Christians

01:27:22.420 --> 01:27:25.420
were in the poverty

01:27:25.420 --> 01:27:29.420
yet they backed for the privilege of giving.

01:27:29.420 --> 01:27:31.420
They were happy to give

01:27:31.420 --> 01:27:33.420
even beyond their means

01:27:33.420 --> 01:27:37.420
because they were giving to Jehovah.

01:27:37.420 --> 01:27:39.420
Being poor meant

01:27:39.420 --> 01:27:42.420
that they individually could not give much

01:27:42.420 --> 01:27:44.420
and yet they understood

01:27:44.420 --> 01:27:46.420
that giving materially

01:27:46.420 --> 01:27:50.420
is an expression of our worship.

01:27:50.420 --> 01:27:52.420
Many of you brothers and sisters

01:27:52.420 --> 01:27:54.420
are like those in Macedonia.

01:27:54.420 --> 01:27:56.420
You have very little

01:27:56.420 --> 01:27:58.420
and yet we see your faith

01:27:58.420 --> 01:28:00.420
by contributing generously

01:28:00.420 --> 01:28:03.420
according to your circumstances.

01:28:03.420 --> 01:28:07.420
No matter how small the amount might be,

01:28:07.420 --> 01:28:11.420
you imitate our generous God Jehovah.

01:28:11.420 --> 01:28:13.420
And you experience

01:28:13.420 --> 01:28:15.420
what one sister described in a letter.

01:28:15.420 --> 01:28:17.420
She wrote,

01:28:17.420 --> 01:28:19.420
all these years

01:28:19.420 --> 01:28:21.420
I have been unable to give

01:28:21.420 --> 01:28:23.420
but small amounts of money

01:28:23.420 --> 01:28:25.420
at the Kingdom Hall.

01:28:25.420 --> 01:28:27.420
Yet she continued,

01:28:27.420 --> 01:28:30.420
Jehovah God has given me back

01:28:30.420 --> 01:28:33.420
much more than I have given.

01:28:33.420 --> 01:28:39.189
Even our young children

01:28:39.189 --> 01:28:42.189
can learn to set something aside

01:28:42.189 --> 01:28:44.189
and give to Jehovah here

01:28:44.189 --> 01:28:46.189
for more weeks.

01:28:46.189 --> 01:28:48.189
We occasionally receive notes

01:28:48.189 --> 01:28:50.189
and letters from these young ones

01:28:50.189 --> 01:28:52.189
who want to give to Jehovah

01:28:52.189 --> 01:28:54.189
and they tell us how they appreciate

01:28:54.189 --> 01:28:56.189
what the organization is doing,

01:28:56.189 --> 01:28:58.189
especially the videos.

01:28:58.189 --> 01:29:01.189
This really touches our heart

01:29:01.189 --> 01:29:03.189
and we can only imagine

01:29:03.189 --> 01:29:07.600
how happy it must make Jehovah.

01:29:07.600 --> 01:29:09.600
Jehovah loves us

01:29:09.600 --> 01:29:12.600
forgiving the best that we have.

01:29:12.600 --> 01:29:15.600
We values even our small contributions.

01:29:15.600 --> 01:29:18.600
Even smaller nations do make a difference

01:29:18.600 --> 01:29:21.600
and are noticed by Jehovah.

01:29:21.600 --> 01:29:24.600
He sees our faith in action.

01:29:24.600 --> 01:29:26.600
In the following video,

01:29:26.600 --> 01:29:28.600
note what moved one couple

01:29:28.600 --> 01:29:38.600
to greater acts of generosity.

01:29:38.600 --> 01:29:40.600
When a disaster struck

01:29:40.600 --> 01:29:42.600
in the north of the country,

01:29:42.600 --> 01:29:45.600
we immediately answered the call for help.

01:29:45.600 --> 01:29:47.600
Seeing our brothers and sisters

01:29:47.600 --> 01:29:49.600
in need was heartbreaking.

01:29:49.600 --> 01:30:06.300
But what really touched our heart

01:30:06.300 --> 01:30:09.300
was the spirit of the local brothers and sisters.

01:30:09.300 --> 01:30:11.300
They were like the Macedonians.

01:30:11.300 --> 01:30:13.300
They didn't have much,

01:30:13.300 --> 01:30:36.039
but they gave generously from the heart.

01:30:36.039 --> 01:30:38.039
When we got home,

01:30:38.039 --> 01:30:40.039
Madeline and I resolved to show

01:30:40.039 --> 01:30:42.039
the same kind of spirit.

01:30:42.039 --> 01:30:48.340
First, our appreciation

01:30:48.340 --> 01:30:50.340
led us to review our contribution

01:30:50.340 --> 01:30:52.340
to the worldwide work.

01:30:52.340 --> 01:30:54.340
I've come up with this figure.

01:30:54.340 --> 01:30:55.340
Is this right?

01:30:55.340 --> 01:31:03.350
Yes.

01:31:03.350 --> 01:31:05.350
That's just like Jehovah.

01:31:05.350 --> 01:31:14.100
We looked for ways to be generous

01:31:14.100 --> 01:31:16.100
to those around us.

01:31:16.100 --> 01:31:29.979
We discovered that we had the means to give more,

01:31:29.979 --> 01:31:53.430
so we didn't hold back.

01:31:53.430 --> 01:31:55.430
And then our congregation was invited

01:31:55.430 --> 01:32:05.699
to help with a special preaching campaign.

01:32:05.699 --> 01:32:07.699
I think we could do a bit more.

01:32:07.699 --> 01:32:09.699
Could we push ourselves a bit further?

01:32:09.699 --> 01:32:10.699
I'd really like to.

01:32:10.699 --> 01:32:13.699
It was within our power to help.

01:32:13.699 --> 01:32:16.699
And that's exactly what we did.

01:32:16.699 --> 01:32:21.739
I'm begging too much.

01:32:21.739 --> 01:32:23.739
No, of course not.

01:32:23.739 --> 01:32:40.819
Did you notice what role faith played

01:32:40.819 --> 01:32:42.819
in this couple's giving?

01:32:42.819 --> 01:32:43.819
For example,

01:32:43.819 --> 01:32:46.819
they put their faith in Jehovah's promise

01:32:46.819 --> 01:32:48.819
to care for them in times of need.

01:32:48.819 --> 01:32:49.819
And so,

01:32:49.819 --> 01:32:51.819
they sat down and reconsider

01:32:51.819 --> 01:32:54.819
their ability to generously give.

01:32:54.819 --> 01:32:58.819
Prayerfully, they decided on their contribution.

01:32:58.819 --> 01:33:00.819
In line with our theme,

01:33:00.819 --> 01:33:03.819
they set something aside.

01:33:03.819 --> 01:33:05.819
Additionally,

01:33:05.819 --> 01:33:06.819
they shared materially

01:33:06.819 --> 01:33:08.819
with their brothers and sisters,

01:33:08.819 --> 01:33:09.819
food items,

01:33:09.819 --> 01:33:11.819
and a nice meal.

01:33:11.819 --> 01:33:13.819
They realized what a blessing it is

01:33:13.819 --> 01:33:15.819
to be used by Jehovah

01:33:15.819 --> 01:33:17.819
in caring for others.

01:33:17.819 --> 01:33:21.189
Brothers and sisters,

01:33:21.189 --> 01:33:23.189
we live in the most exciting time in history

01:33:23.189 --> 01:33:26.189
with never to be repeated opportunities

01:33:26.189 --> 01:33:29.189
to demonstrate our faith.

01:33:30.189 --> 01:33:33.189
It was Nepal compared this with a large door

01:33:33.189 --> 01:33:35.189
that opened up.

01:33:35.189 --> 01:33:38.189
Please think for a moment.

01:33:38.189 --> 01:33:41.189
Has the door to activity opened for you

01:33:41.189 --> 01:33:43.189
to learn a new language?

01:33:43.189 --> 01:33:45.189
Or does it look more like the door

01:33:45.189 --> 01:33:49.189
leads you to move to where the need is greater?

01:33:49.189 --> 01:33:51.189
Did this symposium remind you of the door

01:33:51.189 --> 01:33:54.189
that is open for you to receive training

01:33:54.189 --> 01:33:58.189
at the School for Kingdom Evangelizers?

01:33:58.189 --> 01:34:00.189
Or did it direct you to the door

01:34:00.189 --> 01:34:04.189
for assisting with a theoretical building project?

01:34:04.189 --> 01:34:06.189
And maybe this concluding part

01:34:06.189 --> 01:34:08.189
has reminded all of us

01:34:08.189 --> 01:34:11.189
of our privilege of generously supporting the Kingdom work

01:34:11.189 --> 01:34:13.189
by making donations,

01:34:13.189 --> 01:34:17.819
even if they are small.

01:34:17.819 --> 01:34:20.819
What door is open to you

01:34:20.819 --> 01:34:23.819
so that you are able to expand your ministry?

01:34:23.819 --> 01:34:26.819
Don't feel bad if you hesitate to end up

01:34:26.819 --> 01:34:27.819
this is normal,

01:34:27.819 --> 01:34:28.819
and yet please,

01:34:28.819 --> 01:34:32.819
do not delay entering unnecessarily.

01:34:32.819 --> 01:34:35.819
Don't think you can always reach out later.

01:34:35.819 --> 01:34:38.819
We all do not know what our life will be like tomorrow.

01:34:38.819 --> 01:34:39.819
In other words,

01:34:39.819 --> 01:34:41.819
the door to wonderful blessings

01:34:41.819 --> 01:34:43.819
that is open today

01:34:43.819 --> 01:34:46.819
might be close tomorrow.

01:34:46.819 --> 01:34:48.819
So be courageous

01:34:48.819 --> 01:34:52.819
and enter the door to activity in faith.

01:34:52.819 --> 01:34:54.819
And like many of your brothers and sisters

01:34:54.819 --> 01:34:57.819
who already made these steps in the past,

01:34:57.819 --> 01:35:00.819
you will have no regrets.

01:35:00.819 --> 01:35:02.819
Let us all demonstrate our faith

01:35:02.819 --> 01:35:04.819
by doing all that we can

01:35:04.819 --> 01:35:07.819
for our friend and God, Jehovah.

01:35:07.819 --> 01:35:11.819
And we will enjoy a rich life now

01:35:11.819 --> 01:35:15.819
and will be blessed with an ending life in the future.

01:35:17.739 --> 01:35:18.739
Thank you, brothers,

01:35:18.739 --> 01:35:20.739
for those practical suggestions

01:35:20.739 --> 01:35:25.699
on expanding our activity.

01:35:25.699 --> 01:35:27.699
Let's sing a song that reflects our desire

01:35:27.699 --> 01:35:30.699
to do all we can in Jehovah's service.

01:35:30.699 --> 01:35:33.699
Song number 84 is entitled

01:35:33.699 --> 01:35:35.699
reaching out

01:35:35.699 --> 01:35:37.699
that song number 84.
